As my spouse said, "I love carrots and I love cilantro" -- what's not to like? We'll make it again, although we found that the recipe probably serves twice as many as specified.

Rating: 3
This is a good recipe, and similar to one at our neighborhood Tunisian restaurant. Our Tunisian chef uses fresh lemon juice, garlic and caraway seeds, and that version is delicious. I added the garlic, but sauteed it with the other things, and it was delicious. It is great served topped with feta and drizzled with olive oil. Do take care with the cayenne, however. If you have a volatile variety, it will be too much initially, although the heat fades a bit over a few days. This is an excellent recipe for the vegan or vegetarian in your group.

